    "title": "北美地区 手游投放趋势观察",
    "page_range": "72-73",
    "summary": "This section provides a quantitative overview of mobile game advertising trends in North America for 2025, structured to answer retrieval queries on market growth, creative formats, top-performing titles, and monthly performance tracking.\n\n**Topics & Scope:** North American mobile game ad placement trends, advertiser acquisition, creative volume expansion, video format dominance, monthly fluctuation patterns, and regional market notes.\n**Dates & Timeframe:** January 2025 to December 2025.\n**Key Metrics & Claims:** \n- Mobile game advertisers increased 56% YoY (reaching 7.1W).\n- Deduplicated ad creatives increased 67% YoY (reaching 14.2M).\n- Video creatives account for 77.2% of total ad formats.\n- Monthly data tracks advertiser counts, active creative volumes, and the proportional share of new creatives/advertisers across all 12 months.\n**Entities & Products:** \n- Hit new releases: Solitaire Associations, Journey, Tiles Survive!, Sand Crush.\n- Heavily advertised products: X-Clash, Tile Explorer, MapleStory, TopTop (キングダム 覇道), RAVEN2.\n- Data platform: 广大大 (SocialPeta) Advertiser Analysis Module.\n**Figures & Data Structure:** Two monthly trend charts (Jan–Dec 2025) plotting advertiser count vs. new advertiser ratio, and active creative volume vs. new creative ratio. Includes percentage overlays, system share labels, and a concluding regional comparison note.\n**Evidence Types:** Platform-sourced analytics, YoY growth percentages, monthly time-series metrics, product lists, and comparative market observations.\n**Retrieval Questions Answered:** \n- What were the 2025 YoY growth rates for North American mobile game advertisers and ad creatives?\n- Which specific games are identified as hit new releases or top ad performers in the region?\n- What is the dominant ad creative format..."
  },
