    "node_id": "0131",
    "title": "日韩地区 手游投放趋势观察",
    "page_range": "73-74",
    "summary": "This section provides quantitative market data and trend analysis for mobile game advertising in Japan and South Korea from January to December 2025. It is structured to answer retrieval queries regarding:\n- **Topics & Claims:** Regional ad placement trends, creative format dominance, and top-performing genres. Claims that video creatives (77.3%) slightly exceed regional norms to become the absolute mainstream format, with RPG and simulation/management as leading categories.\n- **Dates:** January 2025 – December 2025.\n- **Entities:** Trending game titles (奇蹟MU, Mahjong Wonders, 江湖有詭, 杖剑传说, 蔚藍星球, 國王很忙, 我的花園世界) and the data source (广大大-广告主分析模块).\n- **Metrics:** 61,000 active advertisers (+51% YoY); 13.4 million deduplicated ad creatives (+55% YoY). Monthly metrics track total advertiser counts, active creative volumes, and the respective percentages of new advertisers and new creatives per month.\n- **Figures/Tables:** Monthly trend charts (Jan–Dec 2025) for advertiser volume and active creative volume, each paired with new-entry ratio percentages. Includes a system/platform distribution chart.\n- **Evidence Types:** Aggregated advertising performance data, year-over-year growth rates, monthly time-series visualizations, and platform-sourced market analytics.\n- **Procedures/Definitions:** None explicitly covered.\nThis section enables precise retrieval of 2025 market scale, growth trajectories, format preferences, monthly activity fluctuations, and specific trending titles within the Japan/Korea mobile game advertising sector."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0132",
    "title": "中国港澳台 手游投放趋势观察",
    "page_range": "74-75",
    "summary": "This section provides a 2025 (January–December) market analysis of mobile game advertising trends in China’s Hong Kong, Macau, and Taiwan regions, sourced from the 广大大 ad intelligence platform. It answers questions regarding market scale, creative format distribution, top-performing titles, monthly fluctuations, and regional player preferences. Key metrics include 111,000 active advertisers (+26% YoY), 19.7 million deduplicated creatives (+42% YoY), and a 70.2% video creative share (noted as the lowest globally). It identifies hot products including Lands of Jail, Top Heroes, Emblem Assemble: Neo, Seven Knights, Re:BIRTH, Chaos Zero Nightmare, and HAIKYU!! FLY HIGH. The section presents monthly time-series data for advertiser counts, new material ratios, total material volumes, and platform/OS distribution (82%/78%). It claims broad genre popularity, high acceptance of Chinese, Japanese, and Korean local IPs, and standout performance for RPG titles. Evidence types include ad intelligence metrics, YoY growth rates, monthly trend charts, and product rankings."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0133",
    "title": "东南亚地区 手游投放趋势观察",
    "page_range": "75-76",
    "summary": "This section provides retrieval-oriented data on Southeast Asian mobile game advertising trends for 2025. It answers questions regarding:\n- **Topics & Metrics:** Market scale and YoY growth (advertisers: 68K, +52%; unique creatives: 11.7M, +69%); creative format distribution (video: 77.7%); monthly advertiser counts and active creative volumes with corresponding new material ratios; OS/platform shares (79%, 77%).\n- **Entities:** Top ad-placing titles (Kingshot, Mafia City, Logicus, Fate War, Legend of YMIR, Water Match); data provider (广大大); comparative regional entity (Middle East games).\n- **Dates:** Full reporting period Jan–Dec 2025; specific peak campaign months for Middle East titles (May, June).\n- **Claims:** Middle East game ad campaigns peak in May/June, rely heavily on recycled classic creatives, exhibit slow iteration cycles, and consistently maintain a monthly new creative ratio below 40%.\n- **Figures & Evidence Types:** Two monthly trend charts (Jan–Dec 2025) visualizing advertiser volume vs. new advertiser ratio, and active creative volume vs. new creative ratio. Evidence is quantitative platform data sourced from the 广大大 Advertiser Analysis Module.\n- **Definitions/Procedures:** None explicitly defined or outlined."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0134",
    "title": "中东地区 手游投放趋势观察",
    "page_range": "76-77",
    "summary": "This section provides a data-driven overview of mobile game advertising trends in the Middle East for 2025, structured to answer the following retrieval queries:\n\n- **Market Scale & Growth Metrics:** What are the year-over-year growth rates and absolute volumes for mobile game advertisers and ad creatives in the region? (Advertisers: 21.1W, +58% YoY; Deduplicated creatives: 29.9M, +54% YoY)\n- **Creative Format Distribution:** What is the dominant ad format type? (Video creatives account for 77.7% of placements)\n- **Top-Performing Titles:** Which specific mobile games are highlighted as hot or trending in ad campaigns? (Vita Mahjong, Zen Color, Bingo Voyage, Legend of Elements, Top Tycoon, Umamusume: Pretty Derby)\n- **Monthly Trend Analysis:** How do advertiser counts, new creative ratios, and total material volumes fluctuate from January to December 2025? (Includes monthly new-material advertiser ratios ranging from 45.4% to 53.3%, and monthly new-material ratios ranging from 42.8% to 50.9%)\n- **Platform/OS Distribution:** What is the reported system or platform share for ad placements? (Listed as 77%)\n- **Regional & Genre Claims:** Does the text reference other markets or genre-specific performance? (Yes, notes Europe as a primary market for puzzle/casual games, with a new-material advertiser share near 80% and a placement peak in 2025Q2)\n- **Data Provenance & Scope:** What is the data source and observation period? (Source: 广大大 Advertiser Analysis Module; Date Range: January 2025–December 2025)\n- **Figures & Tables:** What visual data representations are included? (Monthly trend charts for advertiser counts and material volumes, metric summary cards, and a ranked hot-product list)"
  },
