    "node_id": "0137",
    "title": "南美地区 手游投放趋势观察",
    "page_range": "79-80",
    "summary": "This section provides chart-derived data on mobile game advertising trends in South America, enabling retrieval for the following:\n- **Topics & Entities:** South American mobile game market, advertiser activity, and ad creative deployment.\n- **Dates:** Monthly time-series data spanning January through December.\n- **Metrics:** Monthly advertiser counts (Y-axis scale: 0.0K–40.0K) and the monthly percentage of advertisers launching new ad creatives (Jan: 66.0%, Feb: 63.1%, Mar: 68.8%, Apr: 74.3%, May: 73.3%, Jun: 74.0%, Jul: 72.4%, Aug: 74.0%, Sep: 77.1%, Oct: 79.9%, Nov: 81.4%, Dec: 83.8%).\n- **Claims/Trends:** The proportion of advertisers deploying new creatives demonstrates a consistent upward trend over the year, indicating increasing creative refresh rates in the region.\n- **Evidence Type:** Figure/chart data presenting monthly volume and percentage trends.\n- **Answerable Questions:** What is the monthly trend in mobile game advertiser volume in South America? How does the percentage of advertisers refreshing ad creatives change month-by-month? What are the specific monthly metrics for new creative adoption rates in the South American mobile gaming sector?"
