    "node_id": "0138",
    "title": "媒体声音",
    "page_range": "80-81",
    "summary": "This parent section (\"媒体声音\", pp. 80-81) consolidates industry expert commentary on global gaming market evolution, technological disruption, and strategic publishing shifts. It supports retrieval across the following dimensions:\n\n- **Topics:** Overseas expansion trends, cross-category market competition, AI's impact on game development and operations, product category shifts (heavy vs. light, PC, mini-games), 2025-2026 global mobile/mini-game market dynamics, industrialization pathways, SLG genre evolution, hybrid monetization adoption, and platform ecosystem shifts.\n- **Entities:** Mobile games, short dramas, social/financial apps, AI, SLG titles, Vietnamese/Turkish development teams, PC/Steam/AAA titles, mini-game platforms (TikTok, Douyin), specific titles (*Kingshot*, *X-Hero*), publisher \"冰川\" (Bingchuan), developer hubs (Beijing, Changsha, Guangzhou), and production assets (2D/3D character art, scene concepts, UI icons, dynamic effects, player behavior profiles).\n- **Dates:** 2025 (identified as the SLG breakthrough year and period for industrialization methodology establishment); 2026 (projected timeline for key overseas success factors and TikTok mini-game scale-up).\n- **Definitions/Concepts:** IAA (ad-monetized), IAP (purchase-monetized), IAAP (hybrid monetization), \"A+B\" gameplay fusion (e.g., SLG+casual), \"sub-gameplay UA\" strategy, and hybrid monetization mechanisms (defined by their function in lowering user barriers, expanding audience reach, optimizing LTV, and hedging UA costs).\n- **Procedures:** AI-driven production workflows (rapid generation of 2D/3D assets, UI, and dynamic effects with multi-style transfer); AI marketing/operations pipelines (player behavior profiling, personalized ad material creation, churn node prediction, recall campaign triggeri..."
